In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs discussed a meeting between President Obama and lawmakers to discuss tax cuts and other pressing issues. The President outlined his priority of making permanent tax cuts for the middle class and expressed concern about borrowing money to make tax cuts for the wealthy permanent. The Republicans restated their desire to make the wealthy tax cuts permanent. The President asked Treasury Secretary Geithner and OMB Director Jack Lew to sit down with four senators appointed by Senator Reid, Senator McConnell, Speaker Pelosi, and Representative Boehner to begin discussions. The President expressed confidence that progress could be made through bipartisan cooperation. The briefing also touched on other topics such as the START agreement, cooperation between the two parties, and the situation in Korea.